<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9042">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9042">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Alomya" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Alomya" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Alomya</taxonomicName>
has frequently been placed in its own subfamily, 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Alomyinae">Alomyinae</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Perkins, J. F." journalOrPublisher="Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" pagination="1 - 116" title="Hymenoptera. Ichneumonoidea. Ichneumonidae, key to subfamilies and Ichneumoninae - 1" volume="7" year="1959">Perkins 1959</bibRefCitation>
), or in a separate tribe within the 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ichneumoninae">Ichneumoninae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Diller, E." journalOrPublisher="Entomofauna" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" pagination="93 - 111" title="Bemerkungen zur Systematik der Phaeogenini mit einem vorlaeufigen Katalog der Gattungen (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae)" volume="2" year="1981">Diller 1981</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Selfa, J." journalOrPublisher="Entomofauna" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" pagination="237 - 251" title="Illustrated key to the Western Palearctic genera of Phaeogenini (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae, Ichneumoninae)" volume="15" year="1994">Selfa and Diller 1994</bibRefCitation>
) but a close relationship with 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Colpognathus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Colpognathus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Colpognathus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Centeterus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Centeterus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Centeterus</taxonomicName>
was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wahl, D. B." journalOrPublisher="Journal of Hymenoptera Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" pagination="285 - 293" title="The family-group names of the Ichneumoninae (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae)" volume="4" year="1995">Wahl and Mason (1995)</bibRefCitation>
, with the result that the ichneumonine tribe here called 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" rank="tribe" tribe="Phaeogenini">Phaeogenini</taxonomicName>
took the name 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" rank="tribe" tribe="Alomyini">Alomyini</taxonomicName>
. Based on the molecular phylogenetic results of 
<bibRefCitation author="Laurenne, N. M." journalOrPublisher="Cladistics" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" pagination="442 - 473" title="Direct optimization and multiple alignment of 28 S D 2 - D 3 rDNA sequences: problems with indels on the way to a molecular phylogeny of the cryptine ichneumon wasps (Insecta: Hymenoptera)" volume="22" year="2006">Laurenne et al. (2006)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Alomya" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Alomya" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Alomya</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Megalomya" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megalomya" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="9042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Megalomya</taxonomicName>
Uchida are considered here to comprise a separate subfamily.
</paragraph>
